Incident description: The AV driver made contact with a cyclist traveling in the unprotected bike lane while making a right turn.

The AV driver was traveling in a narrow passageway, when the AV driver approached a stop sign and steered to the right around a parked Honda Element with oncoming traffic approaching and made contact with the Honda.
While approaching a stop sign, the AV was rear-ended by a Honda Civic.
Injury description: The AV driver later experienced neck stiffness, sought medical treatment

Incident description: The AV driver reversed out of its diagonal parking spot in a private parking lot while a Honda Civic was simultaneously reversing out of its diagonal parking spot on the other side and made contact with the right rear corner of the AV.
The AV was proceeding through the intersection when the front of the AV made contact with cardboard debris.
The AV was stopped at a red light when a lane-splitting motorcycle made contact with the AV.

The AV was stopped at the intersection yielding to an illegally u-turning skateboard in front of the AV. While yielding, a bicyclist was coming from behind the AV, looking to the left. When the bicyclist turned his head forward, it was too late to react in time to the stopped AV and collided with the AV. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and hand signaled to the bicyclist to pull over to the closest safe place to park. As the AV driver got out of the car to check the bicyclist, the bicyclist was already on in motion on his bicycle and "fist bumped" the AV driver while passing him and leaving the scene.

The AV was stopped at a red light in the left of two lanes. When the light turned green, the AV began to proceed forward toward the intersection. In the right lane, another vehicle drifted within its lane toward the AV. The AV responded by deceleraring, and a BMW 633 CSi following closely behind rear-ended the AV.
Damage description: Small dent and crack in rear bumper

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight, approaching the intersection, when the AV slowed down. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Honda changing into the AV's lane from the left adjacent lane made contact with the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator later mentioned neck and shoulder pain

Incident description: The AV detected an oncoming pickup truck in its lane. The AV stopped and the pickup truck re-entered the correct lane and passed the AV. The pickup truck was immediately followed by a large group of cyclists in multiple lanes of the roadway, including the right lanes on the wrong side of the double-yellow centerline. The AV remained stopped as the oncoming cyclists rode around both sides of the AV. One cyclist then made contact with the AV and then left the scene.

The AV approached a heavy truck and trailer that was stopped in the adjacent lane on the left side of the street. As the AV began to slowly pass the truck, the truck initiated a reversing turn maneuver into a loading bay on the left side of the street. The AV then came to a stop, and as the AV was initiating its own reversing maneuver to clear the path for the truck, the trailer made contact with the AV.
The AV was traveling straight in a channelized lane when it stopped at the traffic light and a Toyota Prius behind the AV made contact with the AV's rear bumper.
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator on the backseat later mentioned back pain

Incident description: The AV was completing a left turn, a Hyundai Accent behind also turning left tried to pass the AV on the left, and while passing turned back into the AV's lane too tightly and clipped the AV's front left sensor.

The AV was yielding to another vehicle in the left adjacent lane that encroached into the AV's lane, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Honda Accord made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
Damage description: Rear right bumper, fascia, signal lemp and radar assembly
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator later mentioned neck and back injuries

Incident description: The AV made a gradual stop at the stop sign. While waiting, the AV was rear-ended by an Infiniti M35.
The AV driver was proceeding straight through the intersection when a Dodge pickup truck in the left adjacent lane turned right in front of the AV and made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was stopped in a legal curbside parking spot when a Mazda CX-9 approaching from the rear made contact with the AV. The AV was towed from the incident.
The AV driver was following a sharp curve in the road when made contact with a concrete abutment on the right.
The AV driver stopped to yield to an oncoming pickup truck in order to make the left turn. As the truck passed the AV, its driver-side mirror grazed the driver-side mirror of the AV.
The AV driver stopped the AV at a red light when a Ford approaching the rear of the AV at approximately 26 mph collided with the AV.
Injury description: Occupants of the AV reported soreness in their shoulders after leaving the scene

Incident description: The AV after coming to a complete stop switched to reverse gear in preparation for making a multipoint turn. Within fractions of a second, the AV driver applied the accelerator pedal to disengage autonomous mode. The AV then made contact with a Honda Civic that was stopped behind the AV.
The AV was stopped for a red light when a Toyota RAV4 traveling at high rate of speed changed lanes and approached the AV from behind and made contact with the AV.
The AV approached a Ford Ranger that was reversing, the AV stopped as the Ford continued to reverse and made contact with the AV. The AV was towed from the incident.
The AV driver accelerated from the stationary position when parked parallel to the curb and made contact with a BMW 328i.
The AV driver stopped at the four-way stop sign intersection when a Toyota Prius made contact with the AV's rear bumper. The Toyota left the scene.

The AV was stopped waiting to maneuver around a double-parked vehicle. Another vehicle directly behind the AV attempted to pass the AV on the left, and in doing so clipped the left rear corner of the AV.
Damage description: Rear bumper and left rear sensor
Injury description: The AV monitoring operator later reported neck stiffness, but did not seek medical treatment

Incident description: The AV was in the process of passing a mobile crane truck that was double parked. During this maneuver, a Ford F-250 approached and simultaneously went around both the AV and the crane truck. While the Ford made its pass, the AV stopped. As the Ford completed its pass and turned back into the forward lane of travel, the Ford impacted the AV.
Damage description: Front, driver's side sensor and mount

Incident description: The AV was waiting to make a left turn and yielding to oncoming traffic when the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and proceeded with a left turn manually. During the left turn, a Chevrolet Express struck the right side of the AV.

The AV driver approached the 4-way intersection at low speed, a Mercedes GLC 300 did as well from other direction. Both vehicles came to their respective stops at the intersection, then both vehicles resumed movement through the intersection at the same time and came in contact with one another at low speed.

The AV was stopped at a stop sign, then moved slightly forward and slowed down in caution to a pedestrian on its left and potential oncoming vehicles when the driver of a BMW 328 IX made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.

The AV driver parked the AV paralelly to the curb on the side of the street, a Volkswagen Tiguan in the left adjacent traffic lane sideswiped and made contact with the left side of the AV and the parked vehicle in front of the AV.
Damage description: Driver's side mirror, camera, articulating radar assembly and doors

Incident description: The AV driver stopped the AV at the four-way stop, a scooter turning right lost control and collided with the AV.
Injury description: The scooter driver appeared to have scraped her legs, but did not seek medical attention

Incident description: The AV was stopped at a red light when an Isuzu truck turning left made contact with the front left corner of the AV. The Isuzu left the scene.

The AV driver was proceeding with the right of way through a four-way stop, when a scooterist failed to stop at the stop sign and proceeded into the intersection from the right and made contact with the AV.
The AV slowed to a gradual stop with brake and hazard lights activated during a simulated pick up-drop off maneuver when a Honda Odyssey rear-ended the AV.

The AV was stopped at a stop sign when an electric scooter was following closely behind and the scooter driver was not focused on the AV in front of it, the scooter's front tire made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.

The AV driver was traveling on the one-way street when a cyclist turned left and rode into the front of the AV. The cyclist's left turn caused the cyclist to travel in the wrong direction on the one-way street. After contact, the cyclist continued traveling against the one-way.
The AV driver stopped and waited to pass a double-parked vehicle when a Jaguar F-Pace executing a three-point turn made contact with the AV.
The AV driver parked the AV with hazard lights blinking while a BMW 328i reversed from a horizontal parking spot of the oncoming lane and made contact with the rear left corner of the AV.
The AV was on a steep hill, turning right, when its undercarriage made contact with the pavement.
The AV was traveling straight when it approached a partially covered manhole and the manhole cover made contact with the underside of the AV.
The AV driver was going straight through the intersection with the right-of-way, while the driver of Nissan Altima was distracted when it turned into and collided with the AV.
The AV was making a left turn when it encountered a semi-truck flatbed parked in the intersection. The AV made contact with the rear right side of the truck at a very low speed.
The AV driver waited for a pedestrian to clear the crosswalk before making a right turn when a cyclist biked into the rear bumper of the AV. The cyclist continued riding.

The AV was stopped in the dedicated left turn lane, awaiting a green signal for a protected left turn. The signal for traffic proceeding straight turned green, and traffic in adjacent lanes began moving. The left turn arrow signal for the dedicated turn lane occupied by the AV remained red. The passenger car that had been stopped directly behind the AV began moving forward and rear-ended the AV. Immediately after that the passenger car left the scene.
Injury description: The AV driver reported lower back pain

Incident description: The AV driver was stopped at the intersection when a Ford Mustang rear-ended the AV.
The AV driver pulled over in the right lane, when a Land Rover Range Rover that was passing the AV made contact with the AV.
The AV driver stopped the AV in the left turn lane when a Chrysler 300 approaching from the rear in the right adjacent lane collided into the AV. The Chrysler immediately left the scene.

The AV was proceeding straight through an intersection with a green light and right of way when a Nissan Altima attempted an illegal left turn across lanes of traffic into the AV's right of way. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and applied max braking attempt which allowed to mitigate, but not completely prevent the unavoidable collision.
The AV driver was stopped behind a bus in the right lane, when a passenger car that had been stopped behind the AV began to move forward and rear-ended the AV.

The AV driver was stopped at the intersection at a red traffic light when another vehicle making a left turn erratically veered toward the AV, resulting in a low speed collision with the AV. The driver initially stopped and partially opened the drivers door, but then drove away from the scene.
The AV was stopped at a red light when a Toyota Prius approached from behind and rear-ended the AV.
The AV was stationary yielding for an oncoming bus encroaching upon its lane when the bus struck driver's side mirror, causing it to fold with minor damage. The bus driver did not stop.
The AV driver was reversing out of a parked position and struck a pole.
The AV driver was stopped while exiting the intersection as a large truck entered the intersection. While the truck began to make a left turn behind the AV, it made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Rear left radar and camera pod

Incident description: The AV driver was making a right turn when the rear right tire made contact with the lowered loading lift of a heavy truck parked partially across the parking lot entrance.

The AV intended to make a right turn at a green light, to do so the AV slowly decelerated from a low speed and stopped, waiting for a pedestrian to clear the intersection, when a Hyundai Accent made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Driver's side rear bumper and sensor
Injury description: The AV monitoring operator sustained injury

Incident description: The AV was proceeding with the right of way on a green traffic light at the six way intersection when a person operating an electric scooter ran a red light and made contact with the AV, at which time the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode.
Injury description: Emergency services arrived at the scene

Incident description: The AV began to slow down during an uprotected left turn to yield for cross traffic entering the lane from the right when a Ford Fusion coming from behind did not slow and made contact with the rear sensors of the AV.
The AV driver stopped while yielding to a pedestrian, while a Honda Civic LX drove around the left side of the AV in attempt to pass it, clipping left rear sensors.
The AV driver was slowly moving forward in response to an oncoming Hino truck to provide space to pass, while the passing truck came into contact with the AV's rear radar sensor.
The AV driver made contact with the left side mirror of a parked car.
A crowd of people celebrating on the street stopped the AV, painted graffiti on its side and then bashed the windows and threw a firework inside, setting the AV on fire.
The AV traveling straight encountered a double-parked Hino flatback truck. The AV began to maneuver around the stationary truck when it made slight contact with the left rear of the truck.

The AV activated its right turn signal and prepared to make a right turn. The AV stopped to yield to a pedestrian who was in the adjacent crosswalk. A Honda behind the AV made contact with the rear of the AV.
The AV was stopped waiting for a pedestrian to clear the crosswalk, then initiated a right turn, while a Toyota Highlander directly behind the AV rear-ended the AV.
The AV driver, intending to pull out of the parking spot, put the AV into reverse rather than drive and contacted the vehicle parked directly behind the AV.
The AV was stopped waiting for traffic to clear the intersection before making a left turn. A Honda Accord directly behind collided with the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver later experienced neck stiffness, sought medical treatment

Incident description: The AV approached a green light and signaled a right turn when a pedestrian entered the adjacent crosswalk in accordance with the pedestrian WALK signal. As the AV began to slow, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, a few seconds later, a Honda Civis approached from behind and made contact with the AV.

The AV made contact with a downed power cable stretching across the street and came to a stop. Cruise was informed by law enforcement to keep the AV stationary until the power cables were cleared. During the time that the power cable was being cleard and that the AV was stopped, the AV ran low on battery power and did not have enough power to return to Cruise facilities on its own. The AV was therefore towed from the scene once the power cables were cleared.
The AV was traveling through the intersection when an Audi A4 made contact with the AV.
The AV was stopped at a red light when a BMW 325i struck the AV from behind.
The AV made contact with a downed power cable and came to a stop.
The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode to maneuver past an oncoming vehicle that was drifting toward the AV. The AV driver the made contact with an unoccupied parked Honda CR-V.
The AV was traveling straight when a Toyota, completing a left turn, made contact with the left rear corner of the AV. The Toyota drove away.
Damage description: Lower left tail lamp and rear fascia

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when it slowed down, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a cyclist proceeding straight made contact with the rear right fender of the AV. The cyclist left the scene.

The AV was proceeding in stop-and-go traffic through an active construction zone. At the same time, an e-scooter traveling near the right curb was passing other slow traffic behind the AV. Before the e-scooter could also pass the AV on the right, the e-scooter weaved away from the curb, seemingly to avoid a drainage grate, and came within a close following distance behind the AV. As the AV came to a stop again for traffic ahead, the e-scooter rider did not stop and rear-ended the AV. The e-scooter rider remained upright, did not stop to exchange information, and immediately rode off while the AV was still stopped.
The AV was making a right lane change when a Honda CR-V entered traffic from a stop sign intersection on right without stopping and struck the AV.
The AV driver came to a stop behind a Ford Escape that was attempting to parallel park. While reversing, the Ford made contact with the front vehicle sensors of the AV.

The AV was stopped behind a double-parked vehicle in the righ-hand lane of traffic with slow-moving same directional traffic to its left. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and initiated a lane change into the congested left-hand lane. Before the AV driver could complete this maneuver, a Nissan Maximain front of the AV shifted into reverse and proceeded to make contact with the AV.
The AV driver was departing from the Three Embarcadero Center garage facility, as the AV was leaving the garage, the garage gate began to lower and made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was at a complete stop in response to a red light when a Ford Mustang approaching from behind made contact with the AV.
The AV was stopped in traffic for a red light when a Toyota Camry rear-ended the AV.
The AV driver stopped at the traffic light, when a Dodge Challenger traveling at less than 5 mph attempted to bypass the AV from the rear and in doing so hit the AV.
The AV was traveling straight when it slowed down. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, an Audi Q4 made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator later mentioned neck and back pain

Incident description: The AV was stopped at a red light, waiting for traffic ahead with brake light illuminated. When the traffic light changed to green, surrounding traffic began to move. The AV appropriately continued to wait for a stopped lead vehicle immediately ahead, when a vehicle behind rear-ended the AV. The camera footage shows the driver of this vehicle holding their cellphone in their hand at the time of contact.
The AV driver was turning left when a Kia Soul Sport reversed from a horizontal parking spot on the left and made contact with the AV.
The AV was making a right turn when a Ford Ranger made contact with the AV's rear bumper.
Damage description: Rear right fascia and rear center radars
Injury description: The AV driver reported injuries days after the collision

Incident description: The AV driver was traveling in the leftmost lane, as the AV driver attempted to parallel park behind a Hyundai Tucson, the AV made contact with the Hyundai.

The AV was stopped at a red light, when the light turned green, the AV proceeded partually into the intersection, yielding to pedestrians in the left crosswalk while preparing to make a left turn. A Nissa Rogue parked behnd the AV on the right shoulder pulled out of the shoulder and made contact with the right side of the rear of the AV.
The AV driver was proceeding straight in the left lane on a one-way street when a parked Toyota Tacoma on the left side pulled out of the parked position and made contact with the AV.

The AV approached a semi-trailer truck that was stopped in the left lane of traffic. The AV stopped before maneuvering into the bus and taxi lane to pass the semi-trailer truck. As the AV was slowly maneuvering around the semi-trailer truck and merging back into the left lane of traffic, a Honda Accord traveling behind the AV attempted to pass the AV and made contact with the AV. The Honda left the scene.

The AV was traveling in the left lane when a Honda Accord traveling in the right lane behind the AV increased speed and maneuvered across the AV's lane into the parking lane to the left in an attempt to pass the AV. The Honda began to merge back into the AV's lane, the AV braked, but contact was made with the AV. The Honda left the scene.

The AV was passing through the intersection on a green light, when a bag lying on the roadway blew in front of the AV. The AV braked for the object, and a pickup truck traveling behind the AV rear-ended the AV. The pickup truck left the scene. The AV was towed.
Damage description: Rear right bumper, quarter panel, and rear windshield

Incident description: The AV was stopped at a red light, after the light turned green, the AV began to proceed. At the same time, a Hyundai sedan was traveling the wrong way on a one-way section of the street. The Hyundai entered the intersection across from the AV and the AV came to a full stop. The Hyundai continued traveling the wrong way through the intersection and made contact with the AV. The Hyundai left the scene. The AV was towed from the scene.
The AV passed through the intersection, a Vespa scooterist approaching from the rear merged into the lane behind the AV. The AV began to brake, and the scooterist made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Rear window, bumper, right rear headlight

Incident description: The AV was stopped at a stop sigh yielding to a pedestrian in the crosswalk as a passenger vehicle arrived at the intersection from the left. Once the pedestrian cleared the crosswalk, the AV started to proceed at the same time as the passenger vehicle to the left. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, bringing the AV to a stop and a Nissan behind the AV accelerated in the AV.

The AV approached a motorized articulating boom lift, which was stopped in the AV's lane of travel. As the AV began to maneuver around and to the left of the articulating boom lift, the AV made contact with the arm of the articulating boom lift which was elevated above the roadway.

The AV was approaching the intersection prior to making a left turn, yielding to an overtaking vehicle on its left proceeding straight. Once the overtaking vehicle completed its pass, the AV attempted to continue its left turn when a Honda Clarity directly behind the AV, attempting to turn right, made contact with the AV.

The AV was traveling in the middle lane. A slower traveling van in the left adjacent lane began to initiate a right lane change in front of the AV, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and braked. A Honda CR-V EX traveling behind the AV then made contact with the AV.
The AV was traveling straight when a Dodge Journey made contact with the left rear bumper of the AV.
Damage description: Rear bumper and left tail light

Incident description: The AV driver stopped the AV in the right lane of a three lane, one-way street while boarding a passenger. A Ford Fusion behind the AV stopped and then attempted to go around the AV, attempting to merge with traffic in the center lane but colliding instead with a third passenger vehicle and also making contact with the AV.
The AV was waiting for oncoming traffic to clear the intersection before making a left turn when a BMW 633CSi made contact with the right rear corner of the AV.
Damage description: Rear right fascia, bumper and wheel well

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight as it crossed the intersection, a Buick Enclave began closely following the AV. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and stopped the AV. The Buick then stopped, reversed, and drove around the AV and made contact with the AV's rear left fender. The Buick left the scene without exchanging information.
The AV was executing a pullover maneuver and made contact with the left rear bumper of a parked Honda Civic.
The AV was stopped at a red light when a Toyota PK made contact witht the AV from behind.
The AV driver failed to properly navigate a roundabout median and made contact with it at approximately 28 mph.
The AV driver made contact with a Toyota Sienna that was pulling out of a driveway on the opposite side of the street while making a maneuver to avoid a parallel parking vehicle.

The AV driver stopped behind traffic waiting to make an unprotected left turn. The AV driver attempted to make a right lane change to proceed around its stopped lead vehicle and made contact with a Toyota Corolla traveling in the right adjacent lane.
Damage description: Front right bumper and sensor hardware

Incident description: The AV driver was proceeding through the intersection with the right of way when made contact with a Honda Civic that did not obey a stop sign.
Damage description: Right rear passenger door and wheel well

Incident description: While performing a multipoint turn, the AV was reversing at approximately 2 mph when it made contact with an unoccupied parked Nissan.
The AV was making a right turn when a Hyundai made contact with the AV's left rear bumper.
Damage description: Rear upper fascia and lower tail light assembly
Injury description: The AV monitoring operator later reported injuries

Incident description: The AV was about to make a left turn after stopping at the four-way stop sign when a Mazda 3 made contact with the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator later mentioned injuries

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when a vehicle in an angled parking space on the right backed out into the same lane as the oncoming AV. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and pulled to the left to avoid the vehicle backing up. At this time, a cyclist made contact with the rear of the AV.
Injury description: One day after the collision, the cyclist claimed injuries related to the event

Incident description: The AV driver stopped at a stop sign intersection and was yielding to a pedestrian in the crosswalk when a GMC Yukon made contact with the AV.
The AV stopped at a stop sign, when a passenger car approaching from behind made contact with the AV.

The AV was changing lanes into the left turn lane when the AV slowed down. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Hyundai Elantra changing into the same lane made contact with the AV.
The AV was stopped at a four-way stop when a Subaru Outback made contact with the AV's rear bumper.
Damage description: Rear fascia and rear center radar assembly

Incident description: The AV was struck by a golf ball from a nearby golf course to the AV's windshield.
The AV was traveling straight when a Chevrolet, traveling in the right adjacent lane, changed into the same lane as the AV and made contact with the rear corner of the AV.
The AV was stopped at a four-way stop when rear-ended by a Lexus.
Damage description: Cracked a rear sensor plastic casing

Incident description: The AV was traveling downhill when a cyclist approached the AV from behind. The AV began to brake, and shortly therafter, the cyclist made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Rear bumper, rear hatch, and rear window
Injury description: The cyclist sustained injuries, police and emergency medical sevices (EMS) were called, the cyclist was transferred via EMS

Incident description: The AV driver made contact with two parked unoccupied vehicles, damaging the front and rear driver side doors and side mirror of the first vehicle and the front left bumper and wheel well of the second vehicle.
Damage description: Front left radar, bumper, wheel well and wheel axle

Incident description: The AV driver improperly engaged autonomous mode while the AV was in motion, which caused the AV to steer to the right. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and shortly thereafter the AV made contact with a parked Chrysler Voyager.
The AV was parked parallel to the curb on the street when a Ford Econoline van, reversing out of its parallel parking spot, made contact with the front bumper of the AV.

The AV was proceeding straight when a Nissan Rogue struck the AV from behind two times. The Nissan then struck the AV a third time on the left side of the AV as it passed on the left, then immediately left the scene. The San Francisco Police Department is investigating the event as a criminal act.
Damage description: Rear bumper, driver's side front and back door

Incident description: The AV was in the intersection when a Toyota Matrix failed to yield and entered the intersection and made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Front left bumper, wheel, wheel cover
Injury description: A passenger in the AV reported minor shoulder soreness

Incident description: The AV entered the intersection on a green light when a Volkswagen hatchback entered the intersection on a red light and made contact with the AV. The Volkswagen left the scene, the AV was towed from the scene.

The AV entered the intersection on a green light. As the AV was passing through the intersection, a Mercedes sedan entered the intersection on a red light and shortly thereafter made contact with the AV. The Mercedes then made contact with a nearby building, resulting in damage to the property. The AV was towed from the scene.
Injury description: Occupants of the other vehicles received medical treatment at the scene

Incident description: The AV was at a complete stop in response to a red light when another vehicle approaching from the rear made contact with the AV. The driver of the other vehicle left the scene.
The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and waited for pedestrians before making a right turn. While the AV was stopped, a Toyota Tacoma impacted the rear of the AV.
Injury description: The AV monitoring operator later reported wrist discomfort

Incident description: The AV was yielding to oncoming traffic prior to making a left turn when a Subaru Forester made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
Injury description: The AV monitoring operator later mentioned neck pack

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode. Approximately 6 seconds after the disengagement, the AV made contact with an unattended parked Honda Civic.
While performing a multipoint turn, the AV was in reverse at approximately 2 mph when the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode right before the AV made contact with an unnocupied parked Toyota Yaris.
Damage description: Plastic sensor housing on rear passengers side

Incident description: The AV approached the intersection and entered the left hand turn lane, turned the left turn signal on, an initiated a left turn on a green light. At the same time, a Toyota Prius traveling in opposite direction in the rightmost bus and turn lane approached the intersection in the right turn lane. The Toyota was traveling approximately 40 mph in a 25 mph zone. The AV came to a stop before fully completing its turn due to the oncoming Toyota, and the Toyota entered the intersection traveling straight from the turn lane instead of turning. Shortly thereafter, the Toyota made contact with the AV. Police and Emergency Medical Services were called. The AV was towed from the scene.
Damage description: Rear right door, panel, and wheel
Injury description: Occupants of both vehicles received medical treatment for allegedly minor injuries

Incident description: The AV driver was proceeding straight in the right lane when a Honda Civic in the left lane attempted an abrupt lane change at the entrance to the intersection and collided with the AV.
The AV was traveling in the middle lane with a construction backhoe traveling in the adjacent left lane when the AV attempted to make a left turn right in front of the backhoe.
The AV was making a left turn from the leftmost lane when the AV slowed down. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly therafter, another vehicle clipped the AV's right rear corner.
Damage description: Rear right bumper cover, wheel well and wheel

Incident description: The AV was stopped behind stopped traffic when a Fiat 500L ahead of the AV transitioned into reverse and began to accelerate, making contact with the AV.
The AV was at a complete stop in response to a red light when a BMW approaching from the rear made contact with the AV. The BMW left the scene.
Injury description: The AV driver and AV operator later reported back injuries

Incident description: The AV driver was passing through the intersection on a green light when a stand-up scooterist entered the intersection on a red light and shortly thereafter made contact with the AV. The scooterist left the scene.
Damage description: Left front and rear doors and front radar assembly

Incident description: The AV driver was approaching stopped traffic and while attempting a lane change from the far left lane into the center lane, the AV driver partially entered the lane and made contact with a Subaru Forester entering the center lane from the far right lane.

The AV was traveling in the rightmost lane when a Lexus traveling in the middle lane alongside the AV attempted to change into the rightmost lane in which the AV was traveling. Shortly thereafter, the Lexus made contact with the AV. The Lexus left the scene.

The AV was traveling in the leftmost lane of three lanes of traffic, as the AV approached the intersection on a green light, a red SUV traveling in the same direction remained stopped in the middle lane at the intersection. As the AV began to enter the intersection, the SUV made a prohibited left turn from the middle lane, across the left lane in which the AV was traveling and a lefthand turn lane. The AV braked to avoid the SUV turning into its lane and, shortly thereafter, the SUV made contact with the AV. The driver of the SUV laft the scene.
Damage description: Front fascia and front right fender

Incident description: The AV was stopped at a red light, shortly after the traffic light turned green and the AV began to proceed forward, the AV slowed to a stop. A Subaru Outback that was traveling closely behind the AV made contact with the AV. The Subaru left the scene.

The AV began to proceed after the traffic light turned green when an Infiniti Q50 passed the AV in the oncoming lane and began performing "donuts" in the intersection. The AV began to initiate a left turn when the Infiniti made contact with the AV. The driver left the scene. The AV was towed from the incident.
Damage description: Front left bumper, fascia, and headlight

Incident description: The AV was stopped at a red light when a Toyota Prius behind the AV attempted to change into the right adjacent lane and made contact with the right rear corner of the AV.

The AV driver was at a complete stop in response to a red light. When the light turned green, the AV driver began to make a right turn and was yielding to a pedestrian in the crosswalk. Shortly thereafter, a Toyota Camry traveling in a non-turn lane made a right turn in front of the AV and made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was at a complete stop in response to a red light in the rightmost lane when a Mercedes SUV exited a parking lot, pulled behind and to the left of the AV and made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Rear left door and wheel well
Injury description: The AV driver later reported head, shoulder and back injuries

Incident description: The AV driver was stopped in traffic at the intersection when a Lexus made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
Injury description: The AV monitoring operator later mentioned neck and back pain

Incident description: The AV yielded to a public transit bus changing into AV's lane from the right adjacent lane, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Toyota Sienna made contact with the left rear corner of the AV.

The AV was traveling straight when another vehicle changed from the right adjacent lane to ahead of the AV without using its left signal. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly therafter, a Ford Fiesta made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver later mentioned neck pain

Incident description: The AV driver stopped at a red light when a Toyota Camry behind made low-speed contact with the rear of the AV.
The AV driver was traveling straight when a cyclist at a red light entered against the one-way onto the crosswalk to pass behind the AV, clipping the left rear side of the AV.
The AV driver stopped for a red light when a Honda Accord made a contact with left-side of the rear bumper of the AV while attempting to pass to the left into the parking lane.

The AV was proceeding straight when it encountered a double parked United States Postal Service van in lane. The AV came to a complete stop while waiting for an opportunity to merge around the USPS van. Then the van rolled backwards and made contact with the AV. No active brake lights or reverse lights on the van were observed.
The AV was traveling straight, at the same time a Yamaha SMAX motorbike approached from the rear and began to merge into the AV's lane behind the AV, and subsequently made contact with the AV.
Injury description: The driver of the motorcycle reported minor injuries

Incident description: The AV driver was stopped in stop-and-go traffic when a Toyota 4runner rear-ended the AV.
Injury description: The AV operators later reported injuries

Incident description: The AV driver entered the intersection when a BMW 328i went through a red light and made contact with the right front corner of the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver and one of the passengers suffered minor injuries

Incident description: The AV driver was a stationary at a stoplight when a Chevrolet came around from behind and attempted to cut in front of the AV and made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Exterior casing of the front left lidar

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when a Honda Accord began to merge into the AV's lane behind the AV. The AV braked and, shortly thereafter, the Honda rear-ended the AV.

The AV attempted to maneuver into the left turn lane from the second leftmost lane when it slowed to a complete stop. A delivery truck traveling behind and to the left of the AV proceeded forward and attempted to drive past the AV on the left. Shortly thereafter, the delivery truck made contact with the AV. The truck left the scene.
The AV passed through the intersection, a pedestrian looking at his cell phone approached the crosswalk in front of the AV. The AV responded by decelerating, and was rear-ended by a Toyota Corolla.
Injury description: The AV driver later sought medical evaluation for shoulder stiffness

Incident description: The AV was stopped at a red light in the righmost lane when a motorcycle approached from behind and made contact with the AV.
The AV was stopped in traffic when a Toyota Corolla approached the AV from behaind while changing lanes and rear-ended the AV. The Toyota left the scene.

As the AV was approaching the intersection, a cyclist approached, splitting the lane and riding in the wrong direction on the lane line between the AV and a row of parked cars adjacent to the AV. The AV slowed as the cyclist approached and passed, and during this time a taxi Toyota Prius driving behind the AV bumped into the rear of the AV. The taxi driver drove away.
Damage description: Scratches and dent to rear bumper

Incident description: The AV driver was traveling straight when a skateboard escaped control of a nearby pedestrian and made contact with the AV.
The AV was proceeding straight in stop-and-go traffic when the AV came to a stop and a Toyota Sienna rear-ended the AV.

The AV was the lead car stopped at a red light. When the light turned green, the AV began moving forward. Shortly thereafter, a Ford Transit closely following behind ran into the back of the AV. The Ford left the scene.
A jaywalking pedestrian approached the AV and intentionally stepped up onto the hood of the AV while stopped at a red light. The pedestrian then stepped off and walked away.
The AV was traveling straight when the AV slowed down. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Toyota 4Runner made contact with the rear right corner of the AV.
Damage description: Rear right bumper, fender and hatch

Incident description: The AV driver was traveling straight when an occupant of a parallel parked Honda Accord abruptly opened a rear door into the side of the AV.
The AV driver drove in the right most lane when the bus attempted to lane change in front of the AV.
Damage description: Front passenger side sensors and fender

Incident description: The AV was stopped in traffic when a Lexus GS that had been stopped behind the AV passed on the left side, crossing the double yellow line and making cotanct with the AV. The Lexus left the scene.
The AV was stopped for red traffic light when a Toyota Highlander approaching from behind rear-ended the AV.
The AV slowed down and stopped for a parallel parking vehicle ahead, a Honda Accord following the AV then made contact with the AV.

The AV was stopped with brake lights illuminated in traffic. When traffic ahead began to move, the AV was appropriately following the car ahead at low speed when the AV was rear-ended by Nissan Frontier. The Nissan left the scene.

The AV was traveling straight when it slowed down to change into the right adjacent lane due to traffic cones ahead. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a lane-splitting Mazda made contact with the right rear corner of the AV. The Mazda left the scene.
The AV driver while turning right made contact with the curb.

The AV was stopped in the righmost non-HOV lane waiting for the intersection ahead to clear during a green light. The Toyota Prius behind the AV was rear-ended by a pick-up truck, causing the front of the Toyota to rear-end the AV.
The AV driver was traveling straight when a car merged in the lane behind the AV. The AV driver then yielded to a bus and the car behind made contact with the AV. The car left the scene.
The AV was making a left turn, a van directly behind the AV continued straight from the same left turn only lane, clipping the back right of the AV as it passed. The van did not stop.
Damage description: Rear bumper and back right sensor

Incident description: The AV was stopped at the intersection when a Honda Fit rear-ended the AV.
The AV was making a right turn when a Chevrolet in the left adjacent turn lane encroached into the AV's lane and made contact with the AV.
The AV was in the right lane slowing to begin a right turn when a Toyota side-swiped the left front lidar unit on the AV while overtaking at a greater speed from the left adjacent lane.
Damage description: Lidar unit, mount, and front fender and bumper

Incident description: The AV driver was stopped at a red right turn when a Mitsubishi Outlander 4D proceeded and rear-ended the AV.

The AV was making a right turn from lane one when another vehicle crossed from lane three into the AV's lane and hit the AV before making the right turn. The other vehicle did not stop before leaving the scene.

The AV driver was reversing out of its perpendicular parking spot, an Audi Q5 simultaneously reversing out of its perpendicular parking spot on the opposite side of the street made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Left tail lamp assembly and rear fascia
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator reported injuries days after the collision

Incident description: The AV driver approached a double-parked vehicle blocking traffic. The AV driver pulled behind the double-parked vehicle, at this time, a Mazda CX-5 following closely behind the AV passed the AV on the left side and made contact with the AV. The Mazda left the scene.

The AV came to a complete stop at the T-junction stop sign and yielded to oncoming traffic from the left. Due to traffic flow, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and reversed, making contact with a GMC Sierra that had approached from the rear and was attempting to pass the AV to make a right turn.

The AV was approaching the intersection when a Tesla Model 3 exited out of a parking garage into the AV's lane of travel. The AV braked and, shortly thereafter, made contact with the Tesla. The Tesla left the scene.
Damage description: Front bumper fascia and front right wheel opening molding

Incident description: The AV was parallel parked along the curb when it began to pull away from the curb into traffic. As the AV pulled away from the curb, a pickup truck that was traveling behind the AV made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was braking for a red light when a Nissan Sentra traveling behind made contact with the AV.

The AV driver was traveling in the second lane from the left through the intersection, when a Hyundai Elantra in the right adjacent lane made a left turn from a straight-only lane and made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was making a right lane change when a Toyota Tundra continuing straight made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was completing a right turn and slowed to yield to a cyclist approaching from the right, after the AV came to a stop, the cyclist made contact with the AV.
The AV was stopping in traffic when a Toyota Prius from behind made contact with the AV.
The AV came to a stop to yield to an oncoming Honda Pilot in a narrow passageway. The Honda proceeded around the AV and side-swiped it.

The AV was traveling straight when it slowed down, shortly thereafter, another vehicle, changing into the AV's lane from the right adjacent lane, made contact with the right rear corner of the AV. The other vehicle left the scene.
Damage description: Rear right fascia and radar mounting bracket

Incident description: The AV driver stopped at a red traffic light and the AV was struck from behind by a Honda CR-V.
Damage description: Rear right sensor, mount and quarter panel

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when a BMW swerved into oncoming traffic and in front of the AV. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and braked to avoid the oncoming BMW, but shortly thereafter, the BMW made contact with the AV. The BMW driver fled the scene on foot.

The AV driver was making a protected left turn with green arrow when an Infiniti M35 being pursued by member of the San Francisco Police Department, illegally entered the intersection from the opposite direction of travel at a high rate of speed and collided with the front driver's side corner of the AV.
Damage description: Front bumper, front left corner, airbags deployed
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator complained of minor injuries, but declined ambulance transportation

Incident description: The AV driver was traveling straight when the car immediately behind the AV passed on the left. That car made contact with the left-rear bumper. The car left the scene.

The AV was yielding to an oncoming electric scooterist when the light turned from green to yellow. The AV safety driver disengaged autonomous mode to make the left turn manually and, shortly thereafter, the electric scooterist made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Right front and rear passenger doors
Injury description: The scooterist reported soreness and bruising

Incident description: A group of terrorist supporters during the pro-Hamas rally blocked the AV and sprayed genocidal, racist, and antisemitic slogans "Free Gaza" and "Free Palestine" on the sides of the AV.
The AV was proceeding straight after completing a left turn when a Honda Accord, attempting to pass the AV on the left, made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Rear left bumper, rear left wheel well

Incident description: The AV was proceeding straight through the intersection when it was rear-ended by a passenger car that was switching lanes. The other party left the scene.
The AV was proceeding straight in its lane when an occupant of a parallel parked Tesla abruptly opened its rear passenger side door in the AV's side.
The AV driver stopped before making the left turn when a bus in the adjacent lane to the right struck the AV.

The AV was at a complete stop in response to a red light. A Nissan Sentra was also stopped in the adjacent lane to the left of the AV. As the Nissan and the AV proceeded through the intersection after the light turned green, a pedestrian entered the crosswalk on the opposite side of the intersection across from the vehicles and proceeded through the intersection against a red light. The pedestrian passed completely through the AVs lane of travel but stopped mid-crosswalk in front of the Nissan. Shortly thereafter, the Nissan made contact with the pedestrian, deflecting the pedestrian in front of the AV. The AV braked aggressively but, shortly thereafter, made contact with the pedestrian. After initially coming to a complete stop, the AV then moved forward again to find a safe place to stop out of traffic. Because the AV did not identify the pedestrian underneath the AV, it resumed driving at up to 7.7 mph for approximately 20 feet, dragging the pedestrian with it, before coming to its final resting point. The Nissan fled the scene.
Injury description: The pedestrian was freed from underneath the AV by emergency responders and transported to a local hospital for treatment, where she stayed for three months

Incident description: The AV driver was gradually slowing down to came to a stop for a passenger vehicle in its lane making a right turn when a cyclist following the AV attempted to pass the AV on the left side and travel between the AV's driver's side and a faster-moving passenger vehicle in the left adjacent lane. As the cyclist attempted to overtake the AV and was in turn being overtaken by the adjacent passenger vehicle, the cyclist fell between the two vehicles. As the bicycle was falling, the bicycle's fron tire appears to have made contact with the rear driver's side wheel of the AV, and the cyclist appears to have made contact with the side of the other passenger vehicle in the left adjacent lane. The passenger vehicle did not stop and left the scene.
Injury description: The cyclist was transported from the scene and reportedly treated for potential head injuries

Incident description: A Honda Accord, finding a gap in the slow-moving but heavy traffic, turned left directly behind the AV. When the AV decelerated to merge into the left lane, the driver of the Honda, who appears to have been distracted, looking at a person standing on the sidewalk, failed to notice and rear-ended the AV.
Damage description: Rear passenger side brake light compressed into bumper

Incident description: The AV was slowing to a stop with brake light illuminated behind traffic when a Volvo C70 rear-ended the AV at approximately 10 mph.

The AV was traveling straight when a Mazda 5 pulled out from a construction area without yielding. Seeing the Mazda was not going to yield to oncoming traffic, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and unsuccessfully attempted to avoid collision.
The AV was stopped at a red light, while the light was still red, an Acura TL that had been stopped behind the AV began to move forward and made contact with the AV.

The AV was a lead car in the right of two left-turn lanes, with a Volvo V40 directly behind. Both vehicles were stopped at a green light and were waiting to turn left. The signal changed, giving the vehicles a green left-turn arrow. The AV began making the turn and was then rear-ended by the Volvo.
The AV driver decelerated and stopped to let a pedestrian cross the crosswalk, a Ford Explorer behind the AV impacted the rear passenger-side corner of the AV.
Damage description: Wheel encoder broken, rear right tire compromised, rear right bumper scrapped and tended, rear right taillight broken

Incident description: The AV driver was proceeding straight in the right lane when a Toyota Prius aggressively swerved into the right lane, cutting broadside in front of the AV, and came to a complete stop, causing unavoidable impact from the AV.
Damage description: Front left bumper, fender and left lidar sensor

Incident description: The AV was parked in a parallel parking space when a Mazda attempted to parallel park behind it and making contact with the rear hardware of the AV causing no damage.

The AV driver was stopped for a red traffic light with an SUV directly behind. As the signal turned green, the AV driver remained stopped to avoid blocking the intersection as traffic was still stopped ahead. The SUV proceeded to move into the adjacent lane and made contact with the AV. The SUV left the scene.

The AV driver was yielding to a pedestrian before completing a right turn, when an Isuzu truck in the left adjacent lane abruptly turned right and cut in front of the AV making contact with it. The Isuzu left the scene.
The AV was stopped at a red light when a lane-splitting cyclist made contact with the AV. The cyclist did not stop.
The AV was slowing to a gradual stop for a red light when a Chevrolet Express rear-ended the AV at approximately 10 mph.

The AV traveled over a pothole which blew out the front driver side tire and caused the AV to veer into the adjacent parking lane. Shortly thereafter, the AV made contact with a parked Subaru Impreza. The AV was towed away.
Damage description: Front right quarter panel, side fascia, left tire, and rear right quarter panel
Injury description: The passenger of the AV was assessed by medical personnel at the scene but was not transported by Emergency Medical Services

Incident description: The AV driver was making a reversing right turn out of the parking garage when the AV made contact with a dumpster which was next to the curb in the roadway opposite the garage exit.
The AV driver was traveling straight when a parked Cadilac Seville pulled out in front of the AV making contact with the AV's passenger side.

The AV was stopped before the intersection in the leftmost lane of a two-lane, one-way road, yielding to blocking cross-traffic when the light turned yellow. At that point, a Ford Contour that had been stopped behind the AV passed the AV on the left and proceeded into the intersection. While passing the AV, the Ford made contact with the side of the AV. The Ford did not stop.

The AV entered the intersection on a green light after being stopped in response to a red light and continued straight when a cyclist entered the crosswalk. The AV braked to the cyclist and, shortly thereafter, a Toyota traveling behind the AV made contact with the AV. The driver of the Toyota left the scene without exchanging information.
The AV entered the intersection on a green traffic light without yielding to a fire truck approaching from the right with activated lights and sirens responding to an emergency.
Injury description: The AV passenger was treated on scene and transported via ambulance

Incident description: The AV was parked, when a Ford began reversing in front of the AV. The Ford then collided with the parked AV.
The AV was proceeding through the intersection when a Ford C-Max made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator later sought medical attention for neck stiffness

Incident description: The AV driver was slowly approaching stopped traffic ahead when a Chevrolet Malibu in the right adjacent lane started reversing into a parallel parking space. In the process, the front bumper of the Chevrolet scraped the right side of the AV.
The AV was traveling straight when a bus merged into the lane in front of the AV. The AV braked, and a white minivan that had been closely following ran into the back of the AV.
Damage description: Small scrape on bottom of rear bumper

Incident description: The AV driver began to maneuver around a double-parked vehicle by merging left into the center lane, shortly thereafter, a Nissan Juke made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Driver side rear passenger door, front driver side fender, front driver side radar equipment and front driver side bumper

Incident description: The AV driver was slowing for stopped traffic in the right lane of a three lane, one-way street. A passenger vehicle traveling behind the AV attempted to go around the AV to merge with traffic in the center lane, but collided with a Hyundai Accent, after which it then also made contact with the AV.

The AV began to yield to a lane-splitting motorcycle on its left, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, the motorcycle made contact with the AV. The motorcycle did not stop.
The AV was traveling straight when a BMW that had changed lanes to pass it on the left, turned back into the AV's lane too tightly and clipped the AV's front left corner. The BMW did not stop.

The AV was leaving a parking lot when the front of the AV made contact with a chain that was connected between a parking lot road sign and a temporary pole. The road sign fell down due to tension on the chain.
The AV was stopped at a red light and when the traffic light turned green, a Toyota Prius behind the AV rear-ended the AV.

The AV came to a complete stop for a vehicle in the process of letting passengers out that was stopped in the AV's lane of travel. A Smart car traveling behind the AV came to a complete stop behind the AV. A Honda Accord trailing behind the Smart car began to decelerate but made contact with the Smart car pushing the Smart car forward into the AV.

The AV began accelerating from a complete stop when a bicyclist proceeded through the stop sign without stopping in order to make a left turn. The AV began to brake and the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and continued braking. As the bicyclist attempted to complete their left turn, he made contact with the AV.
The AV was preparing to make a left turn, as the AV entered the intersection, it slowed to yield to traffic, a Hyundai Genesis 2.0 approached from behind and made contact with the AV.
The AV driver parked the AV on the right side of the road, a Subaru reversed out of an adjacent driveway and struck the AV.
The AV was stopped while yielding to pedestrians in a crosswalk when a BMW reversed at a low speed from an adjacent driveway into the rear of the AV.
The AV was traveling straight when was hit by the opening door of a parked Honda Civic.

The AV was traveling in the leftmost lane when a Toyota Sienna made an unprotected left turn to merge onto the same street. The AV started to brake, then the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and continued to brake, but shortly thereafter, the Toyota made contact with the AV.

The AV was in the intersection when a silver Toyota Tundra failed to yield and continued to enter the intersection. The AV safety driver disengaged autonomous mode, nevertheless the Toyota made contact with the AV.

The AV had stopped at a stop sign, when the intersection was clear, began to proceed through the intersection. At approximately the same time, a cyclist ran the stop sign and immediately veered left to continue across the crosswalk, where it struck the rear driver's side of the AV. The cyclist stayed upright and immediately rode away.
Damage description: Scratches and marks on the rear drivers side bumper

Incident description: The AV was stationary in stop-and-go traffic when a Dodge Ram traveling behind made contact with the AV.

The AV came to a complete stop at the stop sign. With no other vehicles present at the intersection and having the right of way after the stop, the AV started to proceed left. As the AV was making the left turn, a Subaru quickly approached the intersection, failed to stop for the stop sign and struck the AV. The AV driver disengaged from autonomous mode approximately 1,5 seconds before impact.
Damage description: Driver's side bumper and wheel assembly
Injury description: The AV driver and AV operator sustained minor injuries

Incident description: The AV was stopped and waiting for oncoming traffic to clear the intersection before making a left turn when a Jeep made contact with the AV while attempting to pass it.

The AV was traveling in the right lane when approached an einghteen-wheeler that was stopped in the right lane. The AV began to navigate around the eighteen-wheeler and stopped briefly as it was completing its passing maneuver. Shortly thereafter, a Dodge Charger approached the AV in the left lane and attempted to pass the AV on the lefthand side, making contact with the AV. The Dodge left the scene. The AV was towed.
Damage description: Front left wheel, fender, bumper, and mirror

Incident description: The AV was at a complete stop in response to a red light when a Honda Accord approaching from behind rear-ended the AV. The Honda left the scene.
The AV was traveling toward the intersection and began to brake for the stop sign when a BMW behind the AV made contact with the AV. The BMW left the scene.
The AV was traveling straight through the intersection when a Toyota Corolla encroached into the Avs lane from the right adjacent lane and made contact with the AV.
The AV got stuck in wet concrete and became immobilized.
The AV came to a complete stop for a double-parked sedan in the leftmost lane. The AV began to maneuver and to the right of the sedan, when the sedan reversed in the AV. The sedan left the scene.

The AV was approaching the crosswalk, the yellow light were flashing. The AV slowed, paused briefly before the crosswalk, and the began to proceed. A Toyota Highlander immediately behind the AV alsow slowed and paused. A third vehicle, a Subaru Forester, did not slow and collided with the Toyota. That collision pushed the Toyota into the back of the AV.
Injury description: The driver of the third vehicle intended to seek medical evaluation

Incident description: The AV was at a complete stop in response to a red light when a Ford approaching from behind made a contact with the AV. The drover of the the other vehicle left the scene.
The AV was stopped at a red light, after the traffic light turned green and the AV had begun to accelerate, a Toyota Prius behind the AV struck the rear of the AV.
The AV was stopped at a red light when a Toyota Tacoma that had previously been stopped behind the AV rolled forward and made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was traveling straight when a lane-splitting motorcycle passed the AV and knocked off the AV's front left radar cover. The motorcycle did not stop.

The AV was slowing for a red light when an Infiniti Q60 traveling in oposing direction failed to stop for the red light, entered the intersection, and made contact with a black sedan that entered the intersection on a green light. The Infiniti spun after contact and continued into the AV.
The AV was traveling straight when another vehicle attempted to pass the AV on the right, but crossed into its lane, scraping the AV's right sensor.

The AV was approaching the intersection and when it reached the near-side crosswalk in the dedicated left turn lane, it came to a complete stop at the red traffic light. When the traffic light turned green, the AV moved forward slightly, partially entering the crosswalk, to begin staging for the turn, yielding to oncoming traffic and other road users. While waiting for an adequate clearance in traffic, the traffic light turned yellow. The AV remained stopped, declining to proceed into the intersection and make the left turn. While the AV was still stopped, the AV driver took over manual control and proceeded to make the left turn. About 4 seconds later, the AV driver made contact with a rider on a motorized scooter who had entered the crosswalk from the sidewalk at about 10 mph against both vehicle and pedestrian traffic signals.
Injury description: The rider on the motorized scooter appeared to have sustained unknown soft tissue injuries, but left the scene independently

Incident description: The AV was approaching the intersection prior to making a left turn when the AV slowed down. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly therafter, a Cadillac made contact with the AV.

The AV was traveling at approximately 20 mph in the right lane when it began moving within its lane to the left, and then began correcting to the right, at which point the AV driver decided to take over manual control. After disengaging autonomous mode, the AV driver did not change the path of the vehicle and collided with an unoccupied Toyota Prius that was parallel parked.
The AV was stopped at a traffic light when a Nissan hit the AV from behind and left the scene without exchanging information.

The AV began to slow down as a leading vehicle in the lane was slowing down when a Mazda 3 rear-ended the AV. The AV's vehicle footage shows the Mazda driver holding their cellphone raised in their right hand.

The AV driver began slowing for a red light as it approached the intersection. The AV was in the secong lane from the left on a one-way street. A passenger in a Toyota taxi cab that was stopped in the lane to the left of the AV opened the rear passenger door as the AV was coming to a stop. The edge of the taxi cab's door made contact with the AV.

The AV was traveling in heavy traffic, a BMW X5M behind the AV was changing multiple lanes from the lane to the right of the AV across to the left of the AV. While completing that movement, the BMW clipped the corner of the AV.
The AV approached a parking lot, as the AV turned into the parking lot, its undercarriage made contact with the driveway pavement.

The AV was approaching the intersection when a Tesla Model 3 approached from behind, ran the stop sign and made contact with the rear of the AV. The front of the Tesla made continuous contact with the rear of the AV while both vehicles were still in motion for a short period of time before the Tesla slowed down and separated from the AV. The AV proceeded through the intersection and came to a stop when the Tesla accelerated and made contact with the AV again.
The AV was making a right turn when a vehicle overtaking from the rear switched lanes as it drove in front of the AV and made contact with the front AV's sensors. The other party left the scene.

The AV was proceeding straight through the intersection, which bends to the right, when a Dodge Charger came quickly from behind. The Dodge was in a left-only turn lane immediately to the left of the AV, but instead of turning left, the Dodge tried to overtake the AV and proceed straight as well. At this point, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode. As the Dodge cut off the AV, it scrapped the AV's front sensor. The Dodge fled the scene.
The AV was stopped in traffic for a red light when a BMW 5 coming from behind made contact with the AV. The BMW left the scene.

The AV was at a complete stop in response to a red light. When the AV began to move to make a right turn after the light turned green before yielding to a pedestrian in the crosswalk, an Infiniti sedan traveling behind the AV made contact with the AV. The Infiniti left the scene.
The AV was stopped at a red light with a Mercedes ML350 behind it, also stopped. The AV began moving forward after the light turned green, when the Mercedes collided with the AV.
The AV was waiting at a stop light while a Ford Ranger crept forward slowly into the AV. The Ford driver apologized and admitted he was on his cell phone.
Damage description: Rear bumper, dented edge of the trunk door

Incident description: The AV driver scraped a parked Honda Insight at low speed as he haw pulling into a driveway.

The AV was traveling straight when slowed down in the right turn lane. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, an electric scooterist traveling in the same lane made contact with the rear bumper and fascia of the AV.
The AV stopped behind a double-parked delivery truck was struck on its left side mirror by a passing Volkswagen Passat.
The AV was making a right turn when another vehicle made contact with the AV's left rear corner.

The AV was traveling in the rightmost lane while proceeding straight into the intersection, when a semi-trailer truck traveling in the lane to the left began to make a right turn into the AV's lane without a turn signal. The AV braked and the semi-trailer truck made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Front left side, rear left side, rear bumper

Incident description: The AV driver stopped waiting for pedestrians to clear the sidewalk before making a right turn into a driveway. A BMW 328i that had turned left collided with the AV.
Damage description: Rear bumper and left rear sensor

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when the AV yielded to a parallel parking vehicle ahead on the right. Shortly thereafter, a lane-splitting electric scooterist attempting to change lane made contact with the left rear corner of the AV.
The AV had just made a left turn, when a second Cruise AV operating in conventional mode contacted the rear bumper of the AV.

The AV was stopped at a red light in the right travel lane. After the light turned green, the AV entered the intersection and began a right turn when a lane-splitting motorcycle Honda PCX maneuvered around other traffic and quickly came up to on the rear of the AV, traversing laterally in lane from the left to the right side of the AV. The AV braked and the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode. The Honda then struck the AV and fell to the ground. The Honda left the scene.
Injury description: The motorcyclist seemed to scrape his hand, but declined medical evaluation

Incident description: The AV driver was pulling up behind a Lexus RX350 in the left turn lane when the AV driver accelerated and made contact with the Lexus' right rear bumper.
Damage description: Front right headlight, front center radar and radar assembly

Incident description: The AV was stopped when a Toyota approached it at low speed from behind and struck the AV.
The AV driver was reversing out of the parking space in a Costco lot facility when made contact with a cement pillar.
The AV driver was reversing out of the parking space in a Costco garage facility when made contact with a cement pillar.

The AV was stopped at a red light at the intersection with its left turn signal engaged. After the traffic signal changed to green and while waiting for an opening to turn left, the AV was struck by a Honda from behind. The driver of the Honda stated that he was using his phone and not paying attention.
Injury description: The AV driver, AV operator, and rear passenger reported minor injuries for which they later sought medical attention

Incident description: The AV was stopped in the left turn lane at a red traffic light waiting to complete a left hand turn. As the light turned green, the AV appropriately yielded to oncoming traffic when a Toyota Corolla SE attempted to make a lane change to the right and struck the rear of the AV.

The AV driver observed a cyclist traveling in the wrong direction toward the AV. The cyclist was waving his hands and swerving severely, he appeared to be intoxicated. The driver brought the AV to a complete stop. The cyclist continued weaving toward the AV, collided with the AV and fell over. After getting to his feet, the cyclist picked up his bike and deliberatively hit the bike's front tire into the passenger side of the AV. He then pulled on a sensor on the AV.
Damage description: Wire for sensor pulled off of vehicle, scratch on rear passenger side

Incident description: The AV was executing the right turn when it started to brake to achieve a minimal risk condition due to an unexpected system fault. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and the AV was rear-ended by a Toyota Prius that was also turning behind the AV.
Damage description: Rear bumper, cover and rear radar unit

Incident description: The AV was traveling in the righmost lane as a Mercedes-Benz GLS 450 in the left adjacent lane traveling alongside the AV initiated a right lane change and made contact with the AV. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode just before the contact.

The AV was traveling in the left lane when a Ford E-150 changed into the AV's lane without using its left dignal. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, the AV made contact with the Ford.
Damage description: Front right bumper, fender and wheel well

Incident description: The AV driver came to a stop as a Lexus CT200 was stopped in the wrong direction of traffic. The driver of the Lexus appeared to be asleep. The AV driver made attempts to wake up the driver by flashing the AV's headlights and honking the horn. A nearby cycist also made attempts to wake up the driver. Shortly thereafter, the driver of the Lexus woke up, accelerated forward and made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Front right fender and wheel well

Incident description: The AV driver was making a left turn when collided with a Toyota Prius proceeding through the green light.
Damage description: Front left bumper and wheel well

Incident description: The AV driver was making a left turn when a scooterist, attempting to pass the AV on the left, made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Front left fender, radar and wheel well
Injury description: The scooterist reported injuries, but declined medical treatment

Incident description: While passing the intersection, the AV followed the lane markings, which shift to the left as the road transitions to a one-way street. All lanes shift left at that intersection and are clearly marked. A Toyota Camry traveling behind and to the left of the AV, and gaining on the AV, did not shift left with its lane and instead crossed over its lane boundary and lightly swiped the side of the AV. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode just prior to the impact.
The AV was stopped at the intersection when a Lincoln Town Car chased by police officers crashed into the AV and one other vehicle.

The AV was traveling straight when it slowed down for a passing motorcycle Yamaha YZF-R3. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, the motorcycle made contact with the left rear corner of the AV.
The AV driver was stopped at a red light. When the light turned green, the AV driver proceeded forward, and the BMW i3 behind made contact with the AV.

The AV was traveling in the leftmost lane, at the same time, a Tesla Model 3 traveling in the adjacent center lane veered into the AV!s lane without a turn signal. Shortly thereafter, contact was made.
Damage description: Front right qurter panel, side mirror, side radar assembly

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight in the right lane when it stopped due to traffic ahead in the intersection. Shortly thereafter, a Chevrolet Impala made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Rear left bumper, wheel well, and tail lamp
Injury description: The AV monitoring operator reported back pain, but did not request emergency assistance

Incident description: The AV driver was proceeding straight on a one-way street when a passenger vehicle in the right adjacent lane abruptly cut in front of the AV to make a left turn. The passenger vehicle impacted the AV, proceeded left through the intersection, and left the scene.
The AV driver was slowing for stopped traffic ahead when a Ford Transit traveling behind made contact with the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver and AV operator both sought medical attention at the scene and were transported to local hospitals

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when a cyclist in the right adjacent dedicated bike lane veered away from a wayward pedestrian throwing an unknown object in the cyclist's direction on the crosswalk. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, the cyclist veered into the AV's lane and made contact with the right front passenger door of the AV.

The AV was stopped in lane for a red traffic light. A SamTrans bus, with a front-mounted triple-bike rack extending past the width of the bus on driver's side, was attempting to make a right turn on the street where the AV was stopped. The protruding edge of the bike rack was encroaching into the AV!s travel lane as the bus was executing a right hand turn. As the light turned green, the AV inched forward and attempted to steer away from the bus. Just as the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, the protruding edge of the bike rack made contact with the AV.
The AV was coming to a complete stop in response to stopped traffic when a Chevrolet Astro approaching from behind made contact with the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator mentioned back pain

Incident description: The AV was traveling 24,9 mph upon coming to the intersection on a green light. As the AV entered the intersection, a Range Rover was traveling the wrong way on a one-way street and entered the intersection on a red light. The AV started to brake, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and continued to brake while steering away from the approaching vehicle but, shortly thereafter, the Range Rover made contact with the AV which was traveling 11,2 mph.

The AV was turning left in the outer of two left turn lanes, during the turn, a vehicle in the inner of the two left turn lanes began to cut in front of the AV. The AV braked and a bike that had been closely crossing behind the rear of the AV ran into the back of the AV.
The AV was traveling straight when a Chevrolet Suburban K1500 changing into the same lane made contact with the left rear corner of the AV.
Damage description: Rear left bumper and wheel well

Incident description: The AV was traveling in the second rightmost lane, when a Kia Forte traveling in the adjacent center lane veered into the AV's lane without a turn signal. Shortly thereafter, the Kia collided with the AV. The Kia left the scene.
The AV began to yield to a car on its right, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Toyota Celica made contact with the AV.
The AV was driving in its lane when a motorcycle Kawasaki Ninja 300 tried to overtake it on the left side. As it passed the AV, the motorcycle made contact with the left side of the AV.
The AV was parked at the right side curb when a Nissan Kicks was passing the parked AV in the rightmost lane and made contact with the rear driver's side of the AV.

The AV driver was maneuvering out of a parallel parking spot at the right side curb. As the AV driver reversed, the rear of the AV made contact with the front of a Smart Fortwo parked directly behind the AV.
The AV was turning right while a Lexus RX pulling out of its parking spot behind the AV scraped the AV.

The AV was traveling 24,4 mph upon entering the intersection on a green light. As the AV continued through the intersection, a bicyclist failed to stop for their red light and entered the intersection.
