The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and braked to a speed of 8,7 mph and, shortly thereafter, the bicyclist made contact with the AV.
Injury description: The cyclist verbally reported they were okay, however, the AV driver noticed minor injures to the cyclist. Police and Emergency Medical Services were called, but the cyclist left the scene before the police of EMS arrived

Incident description: While the AV was parked parallel to the curb on the street, a Toyota attempting to park made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was reversing into a parking spot when made contact with the front of a Honda SUV that was parked behind the AV.
The AV driver was approaching the intersection when made contact with the rear bumper of a Toyota Prius that was stopped at the intersection.
Injury description: The AV driver later sought medical evaluation

Incident description: The AV was traveling on the road when a pedestrian ran in front of the AV. The AV stopped for the pedestrian and, moments later, the pedestrian began yelling and approaching the AV. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode to leave the scene. The AV driver drove the AV forward and maneuvered away from the pedestrian, but the pedestrian continued to approach the AV and jumped on the hood of the AV. The pedestrian fell in front of the AV and remained there until later fleeing the scene.
The AV driver hit the curb while making a parking maneuver.
The AV driver stopped in traffic when an Audi A4 rear-ended the AV.
The AV was traveling through the intersection when the AV slowed down. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Mercedes Benz made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.

The AV was parked on the right side of the road. The AV driver inched forward and to the left momentarily, but stopped as two cyclists approached the rear of the AV. As the second of the two cyclists attempted to pass the AV, they made contact with the AV. The cyclist stopped momentarily but then rode away.

The AV was stopped for a passenger pick-up in the AV's lane of travel. After picking up the passenger while the AV remained stopped, a Mercedes-Benz Metris reversed out of a driverway and made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Front left door and auxiliary mirror

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight through a green light when a Mazda, violating a red light, came into the AV's path. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and therafter, the AV and the Mazda made contact.
Damage description: Front bumper assembly, grill, both front wheel wells

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when the AV began to yield to traffic in the left adjacent lane. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Ford Explorer changing into the same lane made contact with the right rear corner of the AV.
Damage description: Rear hatch and window, rear right body and fascia

Incident description: The AV was traveling in the center of three one-way lanes. Identifying a space between two vehicles in the left lane, the AV began to merge into that lane. At the same time, a vehicle in front decelerated. Sensing its gap was closing, the AV stopped making its lane change and returned fully to the center lane. As the AV was re-centering itself in the lane, a motorcycle Honda S90 that had just lane-split between two vehicles in the center and right lanes moved into the center lane, glanced the side of the AV, wobbled, and fell over.
Damage description: Long scuff on passenger side of the vehicle
Injury description: The motorcyclist reported shoulder pain and was taken to receive medical care

Incident description: The AV was at a complete stop in response to a red light. At the intersection, an Acura sedan was stopped in front of the AV in the left lane, to the right of the AV was a BMW sedan. In response to the green light, the Acura made a signaled left turn as the BMW stayed parallel to the AV. As the AV entered the intersection, the BMW made a prohibited left turn from the right lane with no turn signal. The AV braked and, shortly thereafter, the BMW made contact with the AV and left the scene.
The AV was proceeding through the intersection on a green light when a cyclist, traveling through a red light, made contact with the right rear corner of the AV.
Injury description: The cyclist mentioned right shoulder pain, but denied needing an ambulance and left the scene on his own

Incident description: Two passengers had gotten out of a ride share and one crossed while the other stayed behind apparently taking pictures. An SFPD patrol stopped to say something to her, when the AV driver passed in the near lane and hit the other pedestrian who had already crossed, but he probably returned.
Injury description: The pedestrian was concsious and standing after the collision, but went to San Francisco General Hospital for a more accurate diagnosis

Incident description: A masked person approached the AV at the intersection, sprayed the hood, and smashed its rooftop sensors and windshield with a small pick axe.
The AV was traveling straight when a Dodge Sprinter following closely made contact with the AV.
The AV driver completed a right turn, when a motor scooterist made contact with the rear passenger door of the AV.
Injury description: The scooterist reported injuries days after the collision

Incident description: The AV was approaching stopped traffic in the left turn lane when a BMW 4 Series approached from behind and made contact with the AV. The BMW left the scene.
The AV was traveling straight when a skateboarder going through the stop sign made contact with the AV.

The AV driver was traveling in a private parking lot. While he was proceeding towards the parking lot exit, a Toyota Sienna reversing out of its perpendicular spot made contact with the front right side of the AV.
Injury description: The AV monitoring operator later mentioned a back injury

Incident description: The AV turned left into the parking lot when the AV's undercarriage made contact with the driveway pavement.
The AV was traveling straight when a Chrysler Town & Country made contact with the AV's left rear corner.
Damage description: Lower left tail lamp assembly and left rear wheel well

Incident description: The AV was stopped for a red light at the intersection when a BMW 740 traveling behind made contact with the AV.
The AV driver stopped behind a taxi, the driver of the taxi exited his vehicle, approached the AV, and slapped the front passenger window.
Damage description: Scratch on passenger side front window

Incident description: In a heavy stop-and-go traffic, the AV allowed a delivery van to merge into traffic from a gas station parking lot, then with a green light the AV proceeded forward. A pedestrian walking against traffic, off of the sidewalk and in the AV's lane, began to cross street directly in front of the AV. The AV slowed to a complete stop, and a Mazda Protege 5 entering traffic from the same gas station rear-ended the AV.
The AV was traveling straight when a Toyota Prius turning right made contact with the AV.
The AV entered a slip road and came to a stop to yield to cross-traffic. As the AV was stopped, a Volkswagen Passat traveling behind the AV rear-ended the AV.

The AV driver was traveling in the rightmost lane, a Tesla Model 3 at the same time in the adjacent center lane alongside the AV attempted to change lanes in front of the AV over a solid white line into the rightmost lane in which the AV was traveling. During this maneuver, the Tesla made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Rear left wheel and wheel well and door

Incident description: The AV was stopped just left of the right turn lane, with stopped traffic to the right. After waiting to merge, the AV reversed slightly to reroute and while doing so, a sensor on the right fron of the AV made contact with the left rear side of a Kia EV6 in the right turn lane.
The AV began coming to a gradual stop for traffic ahead when a BMW X3 rear-ended the AV at low speed.
Injury description: The AV driver reported a sore neck and back

Incident description: The AV was stopped in traffic at the intersection when a Ford hit the AV from behind.
The AV was proceeding straight when a Lexus turning left struck the AV.
The AV driver slowed to a stop to allow an oncoming box truck International 4300SBA, attempting to turn left, to clear when the box truck made contact with the AV.

Two AVs driven by drivers were stopped side-by-side at the traffic light when a pedestrian in the crosswalk approached both AVs and struck both vehicles with a foreign object, scratching the front right bumper of the first AV and denting the front driver side door of the second AV.
Damage description: Front right bumper, front driver side door

Incident description: The AV driver stopped while waiting to make a left turn when a GMC Acadia rear-ended the AV.
The AV was slowing for a right turn when a following cyclist struck the rear right corner of the AV.

The AV had stopped briefly, initially to simulate the pick-up of a ridesharing customer and then to allow oncoming traffic to pass on the narrow street. After the incoming traffic cleared, the AV began to proceed. At the same time, from behind the AV the driver of a Ford F-250 drove into the oncoming lane and began passing the AV. While overtaking the AV, the Ford clipped a sensor of the AV.
Damage description: Radar and fender on front left side

Incident description: The AV came to a stop at a red light to prepare for a left turn. When the light turned green, the AV proceeded into the intersection. As it did so, a Toyota entered the intersection against a red traffic light at high rate of speed, colliding with the AV.

The AV was approaching the intersection in autonomous mode, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode before reaching the intersection and then proceeded through a green light. A Honda Civic running a red light entered the intersection and made contact with the AV.
The AV began to yield to a car on its left, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a motorcycle Honda CB300F made contact with the AV.
The AV stopped to yield for an oncoming vehicle when a Chevrolet Silverado traveling behind made contact with the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver reported a minor injury, but emergency services were not called

Incident description: The AV driver stopped to yield to makde a left turn when a Ford van made contact with the AV from behind.
Injury description: The AV driver and AV operator reported minor injuries the day after the incident

Incident description: The AV, in the right of two lanes, was traversing the intersection, slightly ahead in the left lane next to the AV, a vehicle drifted into the AV's lane. The AV responded by decelerating, and was rear-ended by a Honda Accord.
Damage description: Small, deep scratch on the rear bumper

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when a Toyota Yaris began to change into the AV's lane. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, the Toyota made contact with the right front corner of the AV.
The AV driver was moving slowly with traffic, when a vehicle merged in front of the AV and in doing so made contact with the AV's front left sensor. The other vehicle did not stop.
Damage description: Plastic casing of the front left sensor

Incident description: The AV came to a stop behind a double-parked vehicle in the right lane. Shortly after coming to a stop, a van approached from behind and made contact with the AV. The van left the scene.
The AV was proceeding on exit ramp in the leftmost lane and entered the slip lane when it came to a stop for a red light at the intersection. A Honda LX which was following the AV rear-ended the AV.

The AV was traveling on interstate when a raccoon ran into the roadway from the left side of the highway in front of the AV. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode shortly before the AV hit the raccoon.
The AV driver was slowing in bumper-to-bumper traffic when a Nissan Altima rear-ended the AV.
The AV yielded to another vehicle that encroached into the AV's lane from the right adjacent lane, and shortly thereafter, a Lexus made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
Damage description: Rear impact bar and a radar mounting bracket

Incident description: While the AV was parked parallel to the curb on the street, a Toyota Tacoma in front of the AV made contact with the front bumper of the AV while reversing out of its parkings spot.

The AV was traveling at 18,8 mph upon coming to the intersection on a green light. As the AV entered the intersection, an Audi A5 made a prohibited left turn from the righmost lane. The AV hard braked prior to the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and continued to hard brake while steering away from the approaching vehicle but, shortly therafter, the Audi made contact with the AV. The AV was traveling 11,4 mph at the time of contact.

The AV entered the intersection on a green light when a Honda Civic initiated an unprotected left turn in the intersection. The AV hard braked but, shortly thereafter, the Honda made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was exiting a parking lot and turning right when made contact with the left rear bumper of a parked GMC Truck.
Damage description: Rear right quarter panel and door

Incident description: The AV driver was reversing when the rear bumper made contact with a stationary and unoccupied Honda Civic.

The AV navigated around a double-parked vehicle stopped in the right lane. After re-entering the right lane, the AV came to a complete stop behind a Kia Optima, at which time the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode. The Kia then reversed into the AV.

After making a right turn, the AV driver pulled over to the right shoulder while waiting for emergency vehicles to pass. A moment later, a passenger vehicle turned right into the oncoming traffic lane and swerved into the driver door of the AV.
Injury description: The driver of the other vehicle was transported by first reponders with injuries

Incident description: The AV was stopped behind stopped traffic in the left-most through lane when a Honda CRV approached from behind and attempted to change lanes into the left turn lane, making contact with the AV.
The AV made contact with a tow dolly attached to the back of a double-parked truck.

The AV came to a stop while yielding to a pickup truck which was reversing into a perpendicular parking space in front of the AV. While the AV was stopped, a GMC van which was in a parking space immediately right of the AV began reversing out of the parking space and made contact with the AV.

The AV was traveling on a narrow road with vehicles parked on both sides and approaching the intersection. A passenger vehicle approaching from the right made a left turn in front of the AV to head in opposite direction. The AV slowed down to a near stop and nudged to its right in order to share the narrow road with the oncoming vehicle and then came to a stop at the stop sign as the oncoming vehicle completed its turn. At approximately 5 mph, the turning passenger vehicle made contact with the AV's sensor hardware housing on the driver side rear corner fender of the AV. Because of this damage, the AV had to be towed. The passenger vehicle left the scene without exchanging information.

The AV was traveling in the rightmost lane when it approached a slow-moving heavy truck equipped with a truck-mounted light matrix displaying a yellow arrow indicating that traffic should merge to the left. The AV slowed down behind the heavy truck and the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode. The AV driver stopped the AV and activated the left turn signal. Several vehicles passed the AV on the left side before the AV driver initiated a left lane change, and a Hyundai Sonata which was passing the AV on the left made contact with the AV.
While trying to merge, the AV was coming to a stop to yield for approaching traffic on the right when the AV was rear ended by a truck.
While attempting to merge, the AV came to a stop to yield for approaching traffir on the right. While stopped, a Hyundai approached from behind and made contact with the AV and left the scene.

The AV was waiting to make a left turn and yielding to oncoming traffic when the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and proceeded with a left turn manually. During the turn, an approaching van made contact with the front bumper of the AV.

The AV was traveling in the far right lane when it passed a Ford F-350 Super Duty pickup truck that was stopped in the bike lane. As the AV passed the Ford, the driver of the Ford opened the driver's side door and the door made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Right mirror and rear sensor housing

Incident description: The AV came to a stop behind a GMC Yukon that was stopped diagonally in the AV's lane of travel. After the AV came to a complete stop, the GMC began reversing further into the AV's lane and made contact with the AV.

The AV came to a stop behind a semi-trailer truck that was slowly reversing diagonally into the AV's lane of travel. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and began reversing, causing the AV to back into a different semi-trailer truck parked behind the AV.

The AV driver was making a left turn when a passenger vehicle attempting to pass the AV on the left side using the oncoming traffic lane made contact with the AV. The passenger vehicle left the scene.
The AV was coming to a stop at a stop sign intersection when a Chrysler 300M made contact with the AV from behind.
Injury description: The AV driver sought medical attention from urgent care the following day

Incident description: The AV driver was approaching slower traffic at the stop sigh intersection and slowed down the AV, when a Chevrolet Astro made contact with the AV from behind.
The AV was slowing for a stop sign when a Honda approached from behind and struck the AV. The Honda immediately left the scene of the event.
The AV was traveling straight when a small dog ran into the street in front of the AV. The AV then made contact with the dog, which did not survive.
The AV was making a left turn, when a Toyota Prius proceeded into the intersection from the left and made contact with the AV. The Toyota left the scene.
The AV driver stopped the AV behind another vehicle when a Chevrolet Bolt behind made contact with the AV.

The AV was traveling at approximately 30 mph in the leftmost lane as it approached the intersection, a city bus traveling at approximately 40 mph in the right adjacent lane began to overtake the AV from the right, while moving toward the AV's lane of travel. Due to the encroaching city bus and the pylons on the left separating the lane from tram line, the AV began to brake. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and took control, one second later, a Ford F-150 behind the AV made contact with the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver was transported to receive medical attention, the AV operator reported minor injuries, but did not receive medical attention

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when a Toyota Avalon passing it on the left merged into the AV's lane too tightly and clipped the AV's front left corner.

The AV approached a double-parked Freightliner semi-trailer truck in the AV's lane of travel. The AV began to maneuver around and to the left of the semi-trailer truck and came to a stop for a stop sign at the intersection. At the same time, the semi-trailer truck proceeded forward and made contact with the AV.

The AV came to a stop behind a stalled bus blocking the roadway. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and began to reverse out of the narrow road. While reversing, a van approached from behind and the AV made contact with the van.

The AV approached a Ford pick-up truck which was oriented with its rear partially in the roadway. The Ford was stationary ut its reverse lights were illuminated. The AV came to a stop momentarily to yield to the Ford, then began moving again to pass the Ford, which had remained stopped. After the AV started moving, the Ford began reversing further out to the driveway and made contact with the AV.

The AV was stopped in the parking lot while yielding to both pedestrians and an oncoming pickup truck. When the truck was passing the AV on the left hand side, it made contact with the AV. The truck then left the scene.
The AV approached a right turn and braked behind stopped traffic. A Mitsubishi Outlander Sport following behind made contact with the rear of the AV.

The AV was proceeding straight when an Infiniti QX70 turned right onto the same street, crossing the center lane line and traveling in the oncoming traffic lane. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and slowed down, then moved to the right most edge of the lane when the Infiniti struck the left side of the AV and immediately proceeded to leave the scene.
Damage description: Front left panel and both left doors

Incident description: The AV was stopped at a stop sign and yielding to a pickup truck that was in the intersection making a left turn when a Nissan Murano traveling behind the AV rear-ended the AV.

The AV was traveling in the slip lane, as the AV slowed to yield to a pedestrian pushing a shopping cart in a crosswalk, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and stopped the AV. The AV driver then proceeded forward but had to yield to approaching traffic in the merge. As the AV driver came to a stop, a Ford F-150 traveling behind made contact with the AV.

The AV was passing through the intersection when a Toyota Corolla which had been previously stopped at a red light proceeded through the red light and made contact with the AV. The Toyota immediately left the scene.
The AV was traveling in the second lane on a four-lane road when the passenger side rear tire made contact with a pothole. The tire began to deflate and the AV pulled over on a side street.

The AV driver was traveling in the rightmost lane when a passenger car approached from behind on the left. Just after passing the AV, the passenger car veerd across the path of the AV into the entrance of a gas station on the right hand side of the roadway and made contact with the AV, immediately after which the passenger car left the scene.
The AV was traveling straight when a Toyota Venza passing the AV to the left initiated a right lane change. The front of the Toyota made contact with the AV. The Toyota left the scene.
The AV came to a stop to yield for approaching traffic on the right while attempting to merge, a Nissan Frontier approached from behind and made contact with the AV.

The AV was completing a right turn when it slowed to a stop while entering a narrow roaway. As the AV started to slowly proceed forwrd, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and proceeded forward, making contact with a parked GMC Envoy.

The AV was waiting to turn right when the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and a passenger vehicle in the process of completing a right turn made contact with the stopped AV before proceeding straight through the narrow roadway. The passenger vehicle left the scene.

The AV had to come to a complete stop at the stop sign in order to yield to traffic. Then the AV proceeded slowly in preparation to merge, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and manually stopped, after that a Volvo 12S made contact with the AV.
The AV driver pulled into the right parking lane to park, while in the process, the AV driver made contact with the bumper of a parked Mazda 3.

The AV driver was reversing on a narrow street in order to make room for an oncoming passenger vehicle to pass when the AV's rear passenger's side sensor housing came in contact with an unoccupied parked Ford Ranger.
The AV driver was waiting at a red light when a passenger vehicle approached from behind and made contact with the AV. The passenger vehicle left the scene.

The AV was stopped in the right lane of traffic behind and to the left of a Hyundai Elantra that was stopped beside the right curb. The driver was standing beside the Hyundai with the driver door open into the lane of traffic. The Hyundai then rolled backwards at an angle and, shortly thereafter, made contact with the AV. The Hyundai left the scene.
Damage description: Right front passenger door, rear passenger door, rear quarter panel, rear bumper, rear wheel

Incident description: The AV driver parked on the right side of the road when a Honda CR-V passed the AV in the traffic lane to the left and began shifting to the right and made contact with the AV.
The AV was yielding to oncoming traffic in preparation to make a left turn on a green light, when a BMW sedan traveling behind the AV failed to stop and rear-ended the AV. The BMW left the scene.
Damage description: Rear right side bumper fascia and wheel molding

Incident description: The AV was approaching the intersection and began to brake in response to a red light when a Honda Civic traveling behind the AV made contact with the AV. The Honda left the scene.
Damage description: Rear fascia and rear right sensor

Incident description: The AV came to a stop to yield to a heavy truck. As the heavy truck drove past the AV, it side swiped the AV. The heavy truck left the scene.

The AV turned right and proceeded straight in the far right lane when a Lexus RX400h made a continuous right lane change from the far left lane, through the middle lane, and entered the far right lane in front of the AV. The AV was decelerating when the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and the AV made contact with the Lexus.

The AV was merging into the rightmost lane, as the AV merged, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and began accelerating. The AV then rear-ended a Tesla Model S that was stopped in the rightmost lane.
The AV came to a stop while yielding for an oncoming Mercedes van in a narrow passageway in a parking lot. While attempting to pass the AV, the Mercedes made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was at a complete stop while yielding to traffic approaching from the left, waiting to make a left turn, when a Chevrolet Silverado rear-ended the AV.
AV came to a complete stop at a stop sign, a Toyota Tacoma then rear-ended the AV.
The AV came to a stop while yielding to an oncoming Toyota Tacoma in a narrow roadway. The Toyota continued proceeding straight and made contact with the AV.

The AV braked in response to a pedestrian in the middle of the intersection, running directly towards the AV. The AV driver, concerned for safety, disengaged from autonomous mode to attempt to move the AV around the pedestrian who was still rapidly heading directly towards the AV in the center of the street. The AV was then struck by a skateboarder who suddenly entered the crosswalk from the sidewalk. Contact was made by the skateboarder to the AV.
Damage description: Front quarter panel area and the articulating radar
Injury description: The skateboarder appeared injured, 911 was immediately called, but the skateboarder left the scene shortly after the incident

Incident description: The AV was stopped for a red light in the right lane of the three-lane street, a Toyota approached from behind and stopped behind the AV before eventually proceeding forward and making contact with the AV.

The AV was passing a Lexus sedan which was stopped in the middle of the road between the AV's lane of travel and opposite lane of travel when the front passenger of the Lexus opened their side door and made contact with the AV. The Lexus left the scene.
The AV was traveling straight when it detected a siren from a nearby emergency vehicle. As the AV slowed down, a Toyota Prius made rear-ended the AV.
The AV was driving in its lane when a cargo truck Isuzu NPR tried to overtake it on the left side. As it passed the AV, the Isuzu clipped the AV's left front articulating radar.
The AV was stopped at a red light when a Ford Fusion immediately behind the AV began to accelerate and made contact with the AV.

The AV was at a complete stop in response to a stop sign. As the AV began to proceed straight, a Honda Odyssey on the opposite side of the intersection from the AV entered the intersection and veered into the AV's lane of travel. The AV stopped in response as the Honda continued traveling in the AV's lane of travel through the intersection and shortly thereafter made contact with the AV. The AV was towed from the scene.
Damage description: Left doors, front left radar assembly, rear left tire

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight through the intersection, a Subaru Outback was traveling in opposite direction, while it crossed the centerline into the AV's path. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and brought the AV to a stop. The Subaru then made contact with the AV and left the scene.
The AV was yielding to oncoming traffic prior to making a left turn when a Honda Accord made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver reported back pain, but did not request emergency assistance, the AV monitoring operator did not report any injuries, but later reported neck pain

Incident description: The AV aproached the intersection as a Toyota Tundra was yielding for pedestrians and blocking the bike lane with two cyclists approaching. The AV braked for the two cyclists as a third cyclist traveling behind the AV veered left to avoind another vehicle pulling out of a curbside parking spot. The third cyclist then made contact with the right rear bumper of the AV, falling off their bike.
The AV driver parked the AV when a Toyota Highlander pulled in front of the AV too tightly, scratching the left front bumper of the AV.

The AV was coming to a stop for a stop sign when a Ford Transit cargo van approaching from the rear failed to stop behind the AV and made contact with the AV. Police and Emergency Medical Services were called. The AV was towed from the scene.
Injury description: The Ford driver was transported by EMS for further evaluation

Incident description: The AV was stopped after having executed a pull-over in autonomous mode, at which time the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and took manual control. The AV driver then proceeded into the driving lane and made contact with the right rear fender of a Toyota Tacoma.
The AV was stopped at a red light when a Volkswagen Jetta approaching from the rear did not come to a complete stop and made contact with the AV. The Volkswagen drove away.
Injury description: The AV driver requested medical treatment

Incident description: The AV changed lanes from the center lane to the right lane before slowing to a stop at a red light. While the AV was making the lane change, a Toyota 4Runner immediately behind the AV in the right lane moved to the center lane and made contact with the right rear sensor of the AV.
The AV driver was navigating a narrow roadway with an oncoming vehicle when the AV made contact with a parked Ford Edge on the right side of the road.

The AV was in the intersection when the AV began to slow for a motorcyclist in opposite direction signaling to make an unprotected left turn. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and continued to slow the AV. The motorcyclist attempted to turn behind the AV and made contact with the left rear corner of the AV. The motorcyclist remained upright and rode away without stopping to provide any information.

The AV was stopped at a red traffic light when a pedestrian entered the crosswalk. When the traffic light turned green, the AV remained stopped for a crossing pedestrian who had just reached the pedestrian island in the middle of the crosswalk. After a brief pause, the AV started to proceed, when a Toyota RAV4 behind the AV made contact with the AV.

The AV began to brake as it approached a stopped van on the oncoming side of the narrow roadway. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and began proceeding straight when the front of the AV made contact with a Toyota Avalon XLS parked along the curb.

The AV in the leftmost lane approached the intersection with green light when an individual riding a motorized scooter proceeded to turn left across the paths of the AV and other oncoming vehicles. The AV began to brake, and the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and brought the AV to a stop. A Ford C-Max traveling directly behind the AV rear-ended the AV. The individual riding the scooter was not hit by any vehicle and left the scene.

The AV was traveling in the leftmost thru lane, adjacent to a dedicated left turn lane on its left. As the AV approached the intersection, it came to a stop behind its lead vehicle. The Toyota Camry behind the AV then attempted to change lanes into the dedicated left turn lane, rear-ending the AV.

The AV was at a complete stop in response to a red light. As the AV was proceeding after the light turned green, a Dodge Charger failed to stop for the red light, entered the intersection, and made contact with the AV. The AV was towed from the scene.
Damage description: Left and rear of the vehicle
Injury description: The Dodge Charger passenger was assessed by medical personnel at the scene

Incident description: The AV had come to a complete stop at the 4-way stop sign intersection before proceeding to make a left turn. As the AV was completing the left turn, a Volvo S60 entered the intersection without fully stopping at the stop sign. The AV began to brake, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and manually stopped the AV just prior the Volvo made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Left front wheel well and driver door

Incident description: The AV driver was proceeding through a green light at approximately 25 mph when a passenger vehicle traveling with no headlights entered the same intersection against the light, making contact with the AV at approximately 14 mph. The other vehicle left the scene without exchanging information.

The AV was stopped in the dedicated left turn lane, awaiting a green signal to turn. The signal for traffic proceeding straight turned green, and traffic in adjacent lanes began moving. The left turn arrow for the dedicated lane occupied by the AV remained red. The Toyota Corolla SE that had stopped directly behind the AV began moving forward and made contact with the AV.

The AV was attempting to make a right turn while yielding to a pedestrian in the adjacent crosswalk. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and shortly thereafter, an Audi Q5 approached from behind, passed on the left side of the AV and made contact with the AV. The Audi left the scene.

The AV was stopped at a red light when a Toyota SUV failed to stop for the red traffic light and entered the intersection, causing a collision with an Acura TSX. The Toyota spun after making contact with the passenger car and collided with the stopped AV. The SUV left the scene.
Damage description: Front left bumper, fender, mirror, and sensors

Incident description: The AV yielded to an electric scooter violating a red light, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, the electric scooter made contact with the right rear corner of the AV.
Damage description: Rear right fascia and brake light

Incident description: The AV was at a complete stop in response to a stop sign, when a San Francisco Police Department Ford Explorer that was in front of the AV reversed from the intersection and made contact with the AV.
The AV driver stopped the AV when a bicyclist riding on the wrong side of the street rode into the front bumper of the AV.
The AV driver was preparing to turn left when the front left wheel rode over a traffic island.
The AV was stopped behind a car that was double-parked and also was yielding to an oncoming car. As the oncoming car approached the AV, it made contact with the AV.

The AV was slowing down as it approached the four-way stop, at which point the driver of a Chevrolet Silverado drove into the oncoming lane and began passing the AV. While driving past the AV, the truck clipped the AV's front driver's-side corner and continued through the intersection in the opposite lane of travel.
Damage description: Scratch on front bumper, damage to sensor

Incident description: As the AV passed through the intersection, a scooter came up from behind the AV and used the right-turn only lane to pass the AV on its passenger side. The scooter entered the AV's lane in front of the AV, and in response the AV stopped. At the same time, an oncoming Subaru Impreza behind the AV attempted to turn left, clipping the rear, driver's side corner of the AV.
The AV was struck on its left rear corner by a Honda Civic making a left turn.

Ahead of the AV, a delivery truck was double-parked in the rightmost lane. The AV began to maneuver round the double-parked vehicle by changing lanes. At the same time, a Honda Civic traveling behind the AV in the rightmost lane also behan to maneuver and increase speed into the leftmost lane. Shortly therafter, contact was made with the AV.
Damage description: Front left side door and radar assembly
Injury description: The driver of the other vehicle later claimed injuries

Incident description: The AV was stopped at a green light in between crosswalks, waiting for pedestrians to cross over the street. A different pedestrian ran across the other street against the "Do not walk" symbol, shouting, and struck the left side of the AV's rear bumper and hatch with his entire body.

The AV was traveling straight when a Ford pickup truck was traveling in opposite direction partially in the AV's lane of travel. The AV stopped due to limited space to procees forward due to the encroaching Ford pickup truck, and shortly thereafter, the Ford pickup truck made contact with the AV. The Ford left the scene.
Damage description: Rear left bumper fascia, quarter panel, and wheel molding

Incident description: The AV was making a right turn when an Audi A4, entering traffic from a curbside parked position, made contact with the AV.
Damage description: Rear right bumper, wheel well, rear parking sensor

Incident description: The AV slowed to a stop due to a pedestrian on a scooter who entered the lane of traffic in front of the AV and started proceeding in circles. Shortly thereafter, the pedestrian approached the stopped AV, placed the scooter on the ground in front of the AV's front ride tire, and walked away off the roadway. After the pedestrian left, the AV attempted to proceed forward and made contact with the abandoned scooter.

The AV driver was preparing to make a left turn, when a passenger car passed the AV and the vehicle directly behind the AV by crossing into and driving in the opposing lane of traffic. As the passenger vehicle passed the AV on the left, it made contact with the AV, after which the passenger car left the scene.

The AV while in manual mode was surrounded by individuals who jumped onto the hood, roof and the trunk of the car and vandalized the vehicle with spray paint. The AV driver was eventually able to direct the AV safely out of the crowd.

The AV was stopped when it switched to reverse gear in preparation for making a multipoint turn, just as the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode by applying the accelerator pedal. The AV then made contact with a Honda Civic behind it.
The AV came to a complete stop at a stop sign, a Toyota RAV4 then rear-ended the AV.
The AV was stopped at a stop sign at the four way intersection when a Chevrolet Silverado traveling behind made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
The AV was making a right turn when a Toyota Sienna traveling straight made contact with the rear driver bumper of the AV.
Damage description: Rear driver bumper and wheel well

Incident description: The AV driver was parallel parked to the curb when a Subaru Impreza pulled up behind the AV. The AV driver reversed to exit the parking location shortly after the Subaru arrived and made contact with the Subaru.
The AV driver was parallel parking when a roof-mounted sensor made contact with a low-hanging tree branch.
The AV was yielding to pedestrians crossing the street when a Ford F-150 traveling directly behind the AV rear-ended the AV.

The AV approached a Toyota RAV4 that was stopped in the lane in front of the AV. The AV began passing the stopped Toyota on the left when the Toyota began reversing in the lane. The AV stopped behind and to the left of the Toyota, while the Toyota continued reversing and began a turning maneuver to enter a parking space. The Toyota then made contact with the AV.

The AV yielded to a jaywalking pedestrian and for clearance to maneuver around a double-parked vehicle immediately ahead of it. While the AV waited, an Isuzu NPR pulling out of a driveway and into the AV's lane made contact with the left rear corner of the AV.
Damage description: Rear left bumper, fender and radar

Incident description: The Av came to a stop to yield to a heavy truck. As the heavy truck moved past the AV, the front left tire of the heavy truck made contact with the AV. The truck left the scene.

The AV was stopped at a stop sign while yielding to pedestrians in the crosswalk. After the pedestrians had crosses, the AV started to edge forward when a Toyota RAV4 to the AV's rear passed the AV by driving in the oncoing lane and made contact with the left rear sensor housing of the AV.
The AV driver attempted to reverse into a parallel parking spot when collided with a parked Audi.
The AV driver made contact witht the traffic island while turning left.
The AV driver was making a right turn when the right rear tire of the AV made contact with a curb at approximately 10 mph.
The AV was stationary for a red light when a Honda Fit coming from behind made contact with the AV.

The AV was stopped in traffic in the left-hand lane when a passenger car that had been stopped behind the AV began moving forward and rear-ended the AV. When the light turned green and traffic began moving, the passenger car left the scene.

The AV came to a stop behind an SUV which was stopped in-lane to load passengers. An Audi Q5 approached from behind the AV and came to a stop. The lead SUV finished loading passengers and proceeded forward, the AV proceeded forward as well. The Audi also proceeded forward and rear-ended the AV. The Audi left the scene.

The AV entered the oncoming lane in order to proceed around a garbage truck and dumpster. The AV driver disengaged the autonomous mode and took control of the AV. As the AV driver was attempting to re-enter the lane in manual mode, the AV's front driver's tire drove over the curb of a traffic island median.

The AV crossed the intersection, the driver of a Toyota Land Cruiser behind the AV drove into the oncoming lane in an effort to overtake the AV. At this point, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode. As the Toyota cut back into the forward lane of travel, the Toyota scraped the sensor on the AV's front, driver's side corner. The Toyota left the scene.
While the AV was stopped behind traffic at a red light, an Audi A3 reversed out of a parking spot perpendicular to the AV and made contact with the rear right corner of the AV.

The AV was stopped at a red traffic light at the unprotected intersection. After the light turned green, the AV began to proceed and then came to a stop as it yielded to oncoming traffic also entering the intersection. A Toyota Sienna made contact with the AV from behind.

The AV was yielding to a pedestrian in the crosswalk, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Ford Taurus attempting a left turn made contact with the left rear corner of the AV.
Damage description: Rear left fascia and wheel well

Incident description: The AV was slowing down for a stop sign, when being almost in a complete stop, a Jeep Compass rear-ended the AV.
The AV was making a left turn when the AV yielded to an oncoming car. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, a Ford made contact with the rear bumper of the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver and monitoring operator later mentioned back and neck pain

Incident description: The AV driver made contact with a passenger side mirror with a parked Honda CR-V.
The AV was yielding to an oncoming Toyota Scion TC. As the Toyota was passing the stopped AV, its driver side rearview mirror made contact with the AV's sensor.

The AV was stopped for a red light with its turn signal activated to indicate intent to turn left. The traffic light turned green and the AV slowly moved forward, yielding to oncoming traffic, when a Nissan Maxima that had been previously stopped behind the AV proceeded forward and rear-ended the AV. The Nissan immediately left the scene.
While approaching a merge, the AV came to a stop to yield for approaching traffic on the left. While the AV was stopped, a Toyota RAV4 approached from behind and rear-ended the AV.
While reversing on a narrow road, the AV driver made contact with the tailight of a parked Honda CR-V.
The AV was at a complete stop in response to a stop sign when a Toyota approaching from the rear made contact with the AV's rear bumper.
Injury description: The AV driver later mentioned neck pain

Incident description: The AV was traveling straight when a San Francisco Municipal Railway (MUNI) bus stopped ahead of the AV. Shortly thereafter, the AV made contact with the bus. The AV was towed from the scene.

The AV driver stopped at a four-way stop sign intersection, signaling to make a left turn. The AV driver yielded to a passenger vehicle to the right, allowing the car to enter the intersection before the AV driver began to slowly enter the intersection. When the car began to make a left turn in front of the AV, the AV driver stopped the AV. A Nissan Sentra behind made contact with the AV.

The AV was traveling through the intersection when a lane-encroaching municipal city bus in the right adjacent lane attempted to pass the AV. The AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, and shortly thereafter, the bus made contact with the right side of the AV.
The AV stopped for pedestrians who were in a crosswalk when a Chevrolet Truck Blazed 4D following behind the AV struck the rear of the AV.
Injury description: The AV driver later reported lower back pain

Incident description: The AV came to a stop sign and waited for a pedestrian to cross and for traffic to clear when a Lexus RX450h approached the AV from behind and made contact with the AV.

The AV was at a complete stop in response to a stop sign. After the AV began to proceed straight through the intersection, a Toyota FJ Cruiser approached a stop sign in its direction of travel. The Toyota did not stop fori its stop sign and, shortly thereafter, the Toyota entered the intersection and made contact with the AV as it was passing through the intersection. The Toyota left the scene.
The AV driver made contact with a steel drain cover while traveling over the cover.
The AV driver was parallel parking when the AV hit the front of a parked Ford F250 pickup truck.
The AV was stopped for a red light in the right lane of the three-lane street when an Acura approached from behind and rear-ended the AV.
The AV driver completed a right turn and turned into a parallel parking space and made contact with the curb.
The AV came to a stop sign and as it was about to proceed, a Lexus CT 200h behind the AV made contact with the AV.
The AV driver was completing a right turn when the AV's rear right tire made contact with the curb at the corner of the intersection.
The AV stopped for a double-parked vehicle, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and shortly thereafter side-swiped the double-parked Lexus RX 450h.
The AV was parallel parked along the curb when a Toyota C-HR pulled up behind the AV and made contact with the AV.
The AV driver hit the curb and drove onto the curb before returning back onto the street.
The AV was stopped at a stop sign when a Toyota Prius made contact with the rear of the AV.

The AV made a full stop at a four-way stop sign. Then the AV entered the intersection and passed approximately 75 percent of it, when a scooterist approached the intersection without stopping and made contact with the rear right side of the AV and then left the scene.
Damage description: Paint scratch on rear right corner

Incident description: The AV was parked at the curb when a Honda Accord in front of the AV began to reverse to parallel park and made contact with the AV.
The AV slowed down and came to a halt at the stop sign. After the AV began to procees, a Honda Pilot approached the AV from behind and made contact with the rear of the AV.
The AV driver was attempting to reverse into a parking spot when the right rear sensor casing of the AV struck a concrete post adjacent to the parking spot.
The AV driver made contact with an unoccupied parked Ford F-250.

The AV was traveling straight, at the same time, a Honda sedan traveling behind the AV maneuvered into the oncoming lane and increased speed as it attempted to pass the AV to the left. Shortly thereafter, the Honda made contact with the AV. The Honda left the scene.

The AV was parallel parked along the curb when a Mazda B2600i that was initially parked directly behind the AV began to maneuver out of its parking spot. As the Mazda pulled out of the parking spot, it initiated a multi-turn maneuver and reversed into the parked AV.
The AV driver slowed the AV while approaching stopped traffic, a Chevrolet approached from behind and made contact with the rear of the AV and then immediately left the scene.

The AV was at a complete stop in response to a red light. After the light turned green, the AV began to make a left turn. While the AV was in the intersection completing the turn, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode and continued straight, and shortly thereafter, the AV made contact with the right curb and concrete guardrail. The AV was towed from the incident.
The AV was stopped in traffic when a Toyota Prius parked to the right of the AV began reversing into the street and struck the AV.

When the AV slowed down at a stop sign, a SUV traveling in the opposite lane crossed the intersection and came to a stop in the opposite lane, next to the AV. After stopping, the SUV began moving again and the front left corner of the SUV made contact with the AV. The SUV left the scene.

The AV slowed for the vehicle directly in front of the AV, which stopped shortly after passing the intersection. Shortly after the AV came to a stop and a Toyota RAV-4 behind the AV was rear-ended by a pickup truck, and the Toyota then made contact with the AV.

The AV was at a complete stop in reponse to a red light when a Honda SUV approached from the rear in the lane to the left of the AV, changed into the AV's lane, came to a complete stop, and then proceeded forward to rear-end the AV. The Honda left the scene.
Injury description: Both AV driver and AV operator reported injuries

Incident description: The AV was stopped in traffic, when a cyclist that had been traveling behind the AV passed the AV on the left. As the cyclist passed the AV, the cyclist made contact with the side mirror. The cyclist did not stop and left the scene.

The AV was traveling in the rightmost lane with a Honda Fit traveling parallel in the left adjacent lane. As the two vehicles approached the intersection, the Honda cut into the AV's lane and braked before turning right. As the Honda executed the right turn, the AV driver disengaged autonomous mode, applied the brakes, but made contact with the Honda. The driver of the Honda left the scene immediately.
